radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal calcium burden in the abdominal aorta and great abdominal arteries. Subcentimeter pulmonary nodules without significant interval change. Gallbladder contains gallstones with mild distension and pericholecystic fluid and stranding. Normal pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands. Normal kidneys without stones or hydronephrosis. Soft tissue density surrounding the area has significantly improved compared to outside hospital CT.
